@node "Intro" "Introduction"

                             INTRODUCTION
                             ------------


    What is Diffmaker & How did it come about?
    ------------------------------------------

    Diffmaker is a little tool I knocked up to create Fidonet Nodelist Diff
    Files. It takes an Old Nodelist, compares it to a New Nodelist, and
    compares the Differences!! It will then Pack the Nodelist using either
    Lha or LZX if required


    In 1995, I started a BBS named @{"DemonáFears" link "BBS" 0} - based in Oldham, near
    Manchester in the UK. After a short while I became involved in a
    Fidonet Style mail Network - 62_NET (Unfortunately, it died a death
    after about three or four months - but hey, I may resurrect it now!)

    My part in this Network was "Nodelist Creator" - But there were
    very few, if any, Nodelist Tools around for the Amiga at that time.

    Another Node in 62_Net, Andrew Bland, DID write a little program named
    smallnl (Included in this archive) - which calculated the CRC check
    and added <CR/LF> to the end of every line, and generally made them
    Fidonet Compliant. Andrew also started work on "Nodekeeper" - A Full
    Nodelist Editor complete with nice looking GUI. As far as I know, it
    never got out of the Alpha Testing Stage, which was a shame because it
    had great potential.

    Anyway - back to Diffmaker. A couple of months ago, I upgraded my BBS
    Software to the Fabulous Zeus BBS Software by Alex May & Nick Loman.
    Zeus, is TOTALLY configurable and uses AREXX for all it's menu's
    scripts, etc... I knew NOTHING about AREXX at that time, but decided
    that I had better learn - Which I am doing, albeit not very well! :-)

    There is a support Network for Zeus named Zeusnet surprisingly, and I
    got to thinking back to when I used to create the Nodelist for 62_Net,
    and wondered if there was a NodeDiff Creation utility knocking around
    anywhere. I looked but STILL couldn't find ANY Nodelist Utilities.
    That was when I thought it might be a nice little project to try and
    write. What a bloody Headache it was - I can tell you!!

    It is now ready for public consumption ;) I have used RMS - The 
    RexxMasher to mash my code really - Not because I don't want people
    pinching my ideas, but because I don't want people looking at my code
    and thinking "What a load of crap - He take 200 lines to write it,
    when I could have written it in 10!!" :-)))

    And there you have a potted history of Diffmaker!!



                              --ooOOoo--
@endnode

@node "require" "Requirements"


                             REQUIREMENTS
                             ------------


    What Do You Need To Run Diffmaker?
    ----------------------------------


    An Amiga would be nic   - As far as I know it works on all versions

    AREXX

    rexxreqtools.library    - Included

    rexxsupport.library     - NOT Included

    LHA & LZX If you require the Archiving Options

    Delete, Rename & Copy in your path somewhere

    A couple of Compiled Nodelists would also be handy!!



                              --ooOOoo--
@endnode

@node "Install" "Installation"


                             INSTALLATION
                             ------------


    What Should I put Where?
    ------------------------


    Erm, all you really need to do, is stick rexxsupport.library and
    rexxreqtools.library in LIBS: (if you haven't already got them) and
    then run Diffmaker!!


    Make sure Lha & LZX are in your path (If required) and also Delete,
    Copy & Rename are in your path somewhere as well..


                              --ooOOoo--
@endnode

