@node "Use" "Usage       "


                                USAGE
                                -----

    How To Use It
    -------------

    Smallnl
    -------

    Included in the archive along with Diffmaker is a little Utility called
    smallnl.

    What this does is stick <CR/LF> at the end of every line if needed, an
    EOF character at the end of the nodelist and most importantly -
    calculates the CRC Check - Essential if using Nodediffs

    What you need to do first of all, is create your Nodelist in a Text
    Editor such as GoldEd, and then save it.

    Then, from a shell type:

            smallnl <filename> <netname>

    So, If you'd saved the file out as Blobby, and the name of the Network
    is BlobbyNet, then you'd type:

            smallnl blobby blobbynet


    It is as easy as that - There is no need to put the day number at the
    end of the filename, smallnl will even do that for you! So, you would
    end up with a file something like:

            blobbynet.138

    Copy that to your Nodelist: Assign, run Traplist (or whatever!) and
    your Nodelist will be compiled!!


    Diffmaker
    ---------


    Ok - so you've created your nodelist and you've compiled it - The week
    after you make your changes to the nodelist, run smallnl over it
    again, and now you want to make a Diffs file.

    There are two ways to run Diffmaker:

    1) Run it with NO ARGUMENTS and you'll be greeted by some REXXREQTOOL
       Requesters, asking you for (In this order):

       The Old Nodelist
       The New Nodelist
       The Directory You want the Nodediffs File Putting in
       A Temporary Directory
       The Name of your Nodediffs File
       Whether you want the Nodediff file Archiving with either Lha or LZX


    2) The other way is to run it from a shell with the following
       arguments:

    diffmaker <oldfile> <newfile> <diffnam>e <outdir> <tempdir> <archiver>

        This way - You are able to run it from a shell automatically once a
        week, and if you archive it up, it is all ready to be hatched out
        or sent out or whatever!!


    The Old Nodelist <oldfile>
    --------------------------

    This is a previously compiled Nodelist with which you want to compare
    This weeks New Nodelist with!


    The New Nodelist <newfile>
    --------------------------

    Your Newly created masterpiece of a Nodelist, with which you want to
    compare with the Old Nodelist!


    The Directory You want the Nodediffs File Putting in <outdir>
    -------------------------------------------------------------

    Self Explanatory really! A Directory for the finished article to end
    up in.


    A Temporary Directory <tempdir>
    -------------------------------

    A place for Diffmaker to keep it's files in while it's working on the
    Node Changes - ALL FILES WILL BE DELETED AFTER USE!!


    The Name of Your Nodediffs File <diffname>
    ------------------------------------------

    If your network is called Blobbynet then you'd probably want to call
    the diffs file "blobbydiff"


    Whether You want the Diffs Archiving <archiver>
    -----------------------------------------------


    Whether you want your Nodediffs archiving using Lha or LZX or whether
    you just want them as they are....



    An Example
    ----------

    oldfile  =  blobbynet.131

    newfile  =  blobbynet.138

    outdir   =  Ram:

    tempdir  =  T:

    diffname =  blobbydiff

    archiver =  Lha


    This would create a Nodediffs file named "blobbydiff.138" (Diffmaker
    takes the day number from the New Nodelist and appends it to the
    Nodediffs), it would then archive it up using Lha to create a file
    named "blobbydif.L38"

    If Using Lha - the first digit of the day number is replaced by "L"

    If Using LZX - the first digit of the day number is replaced by "X"



